Review the knowledge graph against the source document and produce a curation plan.

KNOWLEDGE GRAPH:
{{ kg | tojson(indent=2) }}

SOURCE DOCUMENT (pages numbered from 0):
{{ numbered_pages }}

Return a JSON object with exactly these keys:

{
  "status": "complete" or "needs_improvement",

  "add_entities": [
    {
      "entity_type": "<exact ontology type key>",
      "name": "<name of the missing entity>",
      "reasoning": "<why it should be added>",
      "evidence": "<quote or paraphrase from document>",
      "page_number": <0-based int>
    }
  ],

  "add_relationships": [
    {
      "type": "<ONTOLOGY_TYPE>",
      "from": "<entity name or id>",
      "to": "<entity name or id>",
      "reasoning": "<why it should be added>",
      "evidence": "<quote or paraphrase from document>",
      "page_number": <0-based int>
    }
  ],

  "remove_entities": [
    {
      "entity_id": "<id of entity to remove>",
      "reasoning": "<why it should be removed, e.g. hallucinated, duplicate alias>",
      "evidence": "<supporting evidence>",
      "page_number": <0-based int or null>
    }
  ],

  "remove_relationships": [
    {
      "source": "<source entity id>",
      "target": "<target entity id>",
      "type": "<RELATIONSHIP_TYPE>",
      "reasoning": "<why it should be removed>",
      "evidence": "<supporting evidence>",
      "page_number": <0-based int or null>
    }
  ],

  "update_entities": [
    {
      "entity_id": "<id of entity to update>",
      "attributes_patch": {
        "<attr>": "<corrected or enriched value>"
      },
      "reasoning": "<why these attributes need updating, e.g. alias found, field was null>",
      "evidence": "<quote or paraphrase from document>",
      "page_number": <0-based int or null>
    }
  ],

  "update_relationships": [
    {
      "source": "<source entity id>",
      "target": "<target entity id>",
      "type": "<RELATIONSHIP_TYPE>",
      "attributes_patch": {
        "<attr>": "<corrected or enriched value>"
      },
      "reasoning": "<why these attributes need updating>",
      "evidence": "<quote or paraphrase from document>",
      "page_number": <0-based int or null>
    }
  ],

  "reasoning": "<overall assessment>"
}

Rules:
- attributes_patch must contain the COMPLETE intended attribute dict, not just the changed fields.
- page_number is the 0-based index of the page where the evidence appears. Use null if unknown.
- For alias/duplicate cases: add the alias to the correct entity's attributes_patch under update_entities AND add the duplicate node id to remove_entities.
- Set status "complete" only when all six action lists are empty.
- Use empty lists [] for action categories that have no items.
